<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910221-0178</DOCNO><DOCID>910221-0178.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Gerber Scientific Inc.</HL><DATE>02/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GRB</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)INDUSTRIAL TECHNOLOGY andamp; PRODUCTION, QUALITY CONTROL (ITC)</IN><LP>   SOUTH WINDSOR, Conn. -- Gerber Scientific Inc.'s earningsplunged 86% in the fiscal third quarter as the weak U.S.economy continued to take a toll on its domestic business.   The maker of factory automation equipment posted earningsof $1.1 million, or five cents a share, for the quarter endedJan. 31, compared with $8.3 million, or 35 cents a share, theprevious year. Sales slid 16% to $64.1 million from $76.3million.</LP><TEXT>   Gerber stock fell 50 cents yesterday to close at $9.875 ashare in New York Stock Exchange composite trading.</TEXT></DOC>